Some Frequently Used Library Functions

| Header File  | Function    | Purpose               |
| ------------ | ----------- | --------------------- |
| `<stdio.h>`  | `printf()`  | Print output          |
| `<stdio.h>`  | `scanf()`   | Read input            |
| `<stdio.h>`  | `getchar()` | Read one character    |
| `<stdio.h>`  | `putchar()` | Print one character   |
| `<math.h>`   | `sqrt()`    | Square root           |
| `<math.h>`   | `pow()`     | Raise to a power      |
| `<string.h>` | `strlen()`  | String length         |
| `<string.h>` | `strcpy()`  | Copy a string         |
| `<string.h>` | `strcmp()`  | Compare strings       |
| `<stdlib.h>` | `malloc()`  | Allocate memory       |
| `<stdlib.h>` | `free()`    | Free allocated memory |
| `<ctype.h>`  | `toupper()` | Convert to uppercase  |
| `<ctype.h>`  | `tolower()` | Convert to lowercase  |


